HEADWORD: Teraphim
<hw>Ter"a*phim</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[Heb.
<ets>ter⟦amac⟧ph⟦imac⟧m</ets>.]</ety> <def>Images connected with the
magical rites used by those Israelites who added corrupt practices to
the patriarchal religion. Teraphim were consulted by the Israelites for
oracular answers.</def> <rj><au>Dr. W. Smith (Bib. Dict.).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

